Reference

All functions

Xhalfaversary_insert()

Inserts animal Ids of all primates with each half birth day date from birth until death or the current date into the database table animal.dbl.Xhalfaversary.

add_arc_species_code()

Adds arc_species_code for each animal in character vector id of the provided dataframe id_df.

add_birth_date()

Returns dataframe with POSIXct date vector of birth dates for each animal in character vector id of the provided dataframe id_df. Returns NA in vector if not available.

add_colony()

Returns dataframe with colony for each animal in character vector id for a specified date in colony_date column of the provided dataframe id_df. Returns NA in vector if not available.

add_common_name()

Returns dataframe with and additional column (common_name) corresponding to each animal in the id column of the provided dataframe.

add_death_date()

Returns dataframe with POSIXct date vector of death dates for each animal in character vector id of the provided dataframe id_df. Returns NA in vector if not available.

add_departure_date()

Returns dataframe with POSIXct date vector of departure dates for each animal in character vector id of the provided dataframe id_df. Returns NA in vector if not available.

add_sex()

Returns dataframe with sex for each animal in character vector id of the provided dataframe id_df. Returns NA in vector if not available.

alias_id_to_snprc_id()

Converts an alias (alternate) animal Id to an animal Id.

begin_tran()

Begins a transaction

commit_tran()

Commits a database transaction

create_Xhalfaversary()

Create the database table animal.dbl.Xhalfaversary

create_age_location_sex_species_view()

Creates v_animal_age_location_sex_species as a view in animal database if it does not already exists.

delete_database_record_by_object_id()

Returns logical vector indicating TRUE if record was deleted.

delete_database_tbl()

Returns TRUE if the database table was successfully deleted.

delete_id_from_tbl()

Returns the number of rows deleted from a database table when all the rows associated with a list of names are deleted.

delete_offspring_from_offspring_table()

Returns the number of rows deleted from the offspring table

disable_trigger()

Has the side effect of disabling a specific trigger as defined by type and table name.

drop_Xhalfaversary()

Drops Xhalfaversary table and returns TRUE if the database table animal.dbl.Xhalfaversary was successfully drop

enable_trigger()

Has the side effect of enabling a specific trigger as defined by type and table name.

fill_halfaversary_tbl()

Fill the database table animal.dbl.Xhalfaversary

get_age_dist()

Get the maximum age within a species for a specific date range

get_assignments_to_iacuc()

Returns dataframe with the animals with a status of assigned, hold, or to an IACUC on a particular date.

get_audit_proc_df()

Returns dataframe with audit table data for audit_procedures_entered table of animals for the date range specified.

get_audit_vitals_df()

Returns dataframe with audit table data for audit_vitals table of animals from arrival to death.

get_audit_weight_df()

Returns dataframe with audit_weight data of animals from arrival to death.

get_average_number_of_cagemates()

Returns the average number of cagemates each animal has for days between and including start and end dates.

get_births_in_iacuc()

Returns a dataframe containing the id, sex, and birth date of animals born between to dates inclusive and assigned to a specific IACUC protocol.

get_cagemates()

Returns the cagemates and total number of days together for each animal between and including start and end dates.

get_charge_account_table()

Get charge_account table contents

get_column_names()

Returns a character vector containing all of the column names of for the specified table.

get_common_name_for_arc_species_codes()

Get common name for arc_species_codes

get_common_name_for_genus()

Make a named vector to translate three letter genus and species codes to common_names.

get_common_name_for_species_code()

Returns a character vector of common names using a vector of three character species codes (species_codes)

get_dams_with_infants()

Dams with infants within a specified date range of provided.

get_direct_ancestors()

Get direct ancestors for supplied IDs.

get_dispositions_for_iacuc()

Returns dataframe with the disposition code, disposition description, and count of animals with the disposition code within start_date and end_date inclusive for a specific working_iacuc.

get_female_exposed_to_male_days()

Get number of days females were exposed to fertile males.

get_first_offspring()

Get the first offspring for animals of a specified sex and arc_species_code within a specified date range of provided.

get_id_active_IACUC()

Get IACUCs active for an animal on a specified date.

get_id_clinical_admit()

Get clinical admissions active for an animal on a specified date.

get_id_str()

Returns the character string corresponding to the animal Id columns for specific tables.

get_ids_having_specific_char()

Returns dataframe with animals having a specific character in their permanent Id.

get_location_on_date()

Get location from animal.dbo.location for each animal on the date specified.

get_maintenance_iacuc()

Get dataframe with maintenance IACUC protocols including arc_num_seq, arc_num_genus, working_iacuc, and iacuc_type.

get_max_age()

Get the maximum age within a species for a specific date range

get_non_productive_animals()

Get non-productive animals of a specified sex, arc_species_code, and age.

get_number_of_cagemates()

Returns the number of cagemates each animal has for each day between and including start and end dates.

get_object_ids_in_tbl()

Returns a character vector of OBJECT_ID values from a character vector (o_ids) that were found to be in the database table being queried.

get_object_ids_not_in_tbl()

Returns a character vector of OBJECT_ID values from a character vector (o_ids) that were not found to be in the database table being queried.

get_proc_df()

Get procedure data for animals within date ranges.

get_rearing()

Get rearing code and rearing description for Ids provided.

get_relatives()

Returns a data frame containing four columns: id, sire_id, dam_id, sex when given a character vector of one or more Ids in ids.

get_siblings()

Returns data frame with specified siblings for Ids provided.

get_table_names()

Returns a character vector of table names for the database connection conn where the names do not include specified strings.

get_table_names_w_id_col()

Returns a character vector of table names for the database connection conn where the names do not include specified strings, each table has a column with the name 'id', and the master table is listed first.

get_table_w_col()

Returns a character vector of tables names for the database connection conn where the tables contain a column matching a specific regular expression.

get_tables_and_columns()

Get tables and columns for a database connection.

get_tables_views_and_columns()

Get tables, views, and columns for a database connection.

get_tables_with_data()

Returns a dataframe with a character vector listing the table names and an integer vector indicating the number of rows for those tables having at least one record with values for the animals of interest.

get_tran_count()

Get TRANSACTION count

get_trigger_name()

Returns a character vector with one trigger name af a specific type for each table name provided.

get_vasectomized_males()

Get vasectomized males of a specified arc_species_code that died after a specified date.

get_view_names()

Returns a character vector of view names for the database connection conn where the names do not include specified strings.

get_vitals_df()

Returns dataframe with vitals, date_tm of collection, user name (user_n), and entry_date_tm of animals from arrival to death.

get_weight_df()

Returns dataframe with weights, date_tm of collection, user name (user_n), and entry_date_tm of animals from arrival to death.

has_id_column()

Returns a logical vector indicating whether or not each table contains a column named 'id'.

is_animal_alive()

Returns logical vector indicating if id is animal in master and alive on the provided date.

is_animal_id()

Returns logical vector indicating if animal ids are in master.

is_bad_animal_id()

Returns the proported animal Id(s) that cannot be found in the master table of the animal database.

is_database_tbl()

Returns TRUE if table exist and FALSE if it does not

is_database_view()

Returns TRUE if view exist and FALSE if it does not

is_location()

Returns logical vector indicating if a location exists.

is_primate_id()

Returns logical vector indicating if animal ids represent a primate.

remove_housekeeping_columns()

Returns a character vector with the column_names vector having had all housekeeping columns removed.

rollback_tran()

Rollsback a transaction, returns FALSE if there is not a transaction to rollback otherwise TRUE'

row_exist()

Returns logical vector of length one indication whether or not at least one record exists in the table having an id equal to the value of id.

rows_with_id_in_table()

Returns integer vector of length one indicating the number of records that exists in the table having an id equal to the value of id.

update_ids_in_tables_by_id()

Returns the number of rows updated when old Ids are replaced by replacement Ids in one or more database tables.
